==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Annotate
<hw>An"no*tate</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp.
& p. p.</pos> <conjf>Annotated</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Annotating</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L. <ets>annotatus</ets>; p.
p. of <ets>annotare</ets> to annotate; <ets>ad</ets> + <ets>notare</ets>
to mark, <ets>nota</ets> mark. See <er>Note</er>, <pos>n.</pos>]</ety>
<def>To explain or criticize by notes; <as>as, to <ex>annotate</ex> the
works of Bacon</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Annotate</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Annotate
<hw>An"no*tate</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To make notes or comments; --
with <xex>on</xex> or <xex>upon</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>annotating</ent>⟦br⟧
